const _pharmaceutical_glitches = {title: "Pharmaceutical Glitches", parent_topics: ["gm_specific_campaigns","technological_equipment","timeworn_technology"], siblings: ["armor_glitches","weapon_glitches","pharmaceutical_glitches","general_glitches"], jsx: <><p><strong>Sources</strong> <Link to="/source/technology_guide">Technology Guide pg. 1</Link><br/>Timeworn pharmaceuticals have a chance of glitching when the dose is administered, even if another dose was recently used effectively.</p>
<ScrollContainer id="rule-pharmaceutical_glitches--table-0"><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>d%</th>
<th>Glitch</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td>01-02</td>
<td>Spoiled. Treat as poisoning by <Link to="/eq-poison/dark_reaver_powder">dark reaver powder</Link>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>03-11</td>
<td>Spoiled. Treat as exposure to <Link to="/disease/red_ache">red ache</Link>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>12-20</td>
<td>Spoiled. Patient is <Link to="/misc/nauseated">nauseated</Link> for 1d6 rounds.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>21-30</td>
<td>Spoiled. Patient <Link to="/misc/sickened">sickened</Link> for 1d6 &times; 10 minutes.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>31-40</td>
<td>Spoiled. No effect.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>41-50</td>
<td>Less potent. Decrease all save DCs by 2.<sup><InnerLink showBacklink="backlink-rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-ref-C-1" id="rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-ref-C-1" data-hash-target to="rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-C">1</InnerLink></sup> Use minimum values for all random results (such as healing). Decrease durations by 50%.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>51-60</td>
<td>Normal effect, but causes 1d4 points of <Link to="/rule/constitution_damage">Constitution damage</Link> (Fortitude DC 15 half).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>61-75</td>
<td>Normal effect, but hallucinogenic (-5 penalty on <Link to="/skill/perception">Perception</Link> checks and <Link to="/misc/confused">confused</Link> for 2d4 rounds, Fortitude DC 15 negates).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>76-85</td>
<td>Normal effect.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>86-95</td>
<td>More potent. Increase any save DCs by 2.<sup><InnerLink showBacklink="backlink-rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-ref-C-2" id="rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-ref-C-2" data-hash-target to="rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-C">1</InnerLink></sup> Reroll any result of 1. Increase durations by 100%.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>99-100</td>
<td>Far more potent. As above, but treat as 2 doses.</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table></ScrollContainer>
<section data-footnotes>
<h3 id="rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-label">Footnotes</h3>
<ol>
<li id="rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-C">
<p>For a <Link to="/tech-pharma/cardioamp">cardioamp</Link>, decrease the save DCs on a more potent result, and increase the save DCs on a less potent result. <InnerLink id="backlink-rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-ref-C-1" data-hash-target to="rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-ref-C-1" aria-label="Back to reference C-1">↩</InnerLink> <InnerLink id="backlink-rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-ref-C-2" data-hash-target to="rule-pharmaceutical_glitches-ref-C-2" aria-label="Back to reference C-2">↩<sup>2</sup></InnerLink></p>
</li>
</ol>
</section>
</>};
